    <h1>iPhone Setup Guide</h1>

    <p>This page provides a step-by-step guide to setting up your new iPhone.</p>

    <ol>
        <li>
            <h4>Turn on your iPhone</h4>
            <p>Press and hold the side button (or top button on older models) until the Apple logo appears.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Choose your language</h4>
            <p>Select your preferred language from the list.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Connect to Wi-Fi</h4>
            <p>Select your Wi-Fi network and enter the password.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Set up Face ID or Touch ID</h4>
            <p>Follow the on-screen instructions to set up facial recognition or fingerprint authentication.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Sign in with your Apple ID</h4>
            <p>Enter your Apple ID and password, or create a new one.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Restore from backup or set up as new</h4>
            <p>Choose to restore from a previous iCloud or iTunes backup, or set up your iPhone as a new device.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Agree to terms and conditions</h4>
            <p>Review and accept the terms and conditions for Apple services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4>Customize your iPhone</h4>
            <p>Choose your wallpaper, app layout, and other preferences.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <p>For more detailed instructions and troubleshooting tips, please refer to the official Apple Support website.</p>
